20it%3F%20It's%20a%20bit%20about%20what%20the%20person%20might%20be%20doing%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20about%20how%20the%20person's%20receiving%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20before%20you%20decide%20your%20friendship%20is%20%26quot%3Btoxic%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20you%20need%20to%20set%20some%20new%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fboundaries-in-relationships%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboundaries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Holmes%20shared%20three%20signs%20that%20your%20friendship%20is%20healthy%2C%20even%20if%20your%20friend%20is%20getting%20on%20your%20nerves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHealthy%20disagreement%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20strong%20foundation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20friendship%20where%20you%20get%20annoyed%20at%20each%20other%20but%20you're%20able%20to%20express%20it%2C%20that's%20actually%20quite%20a%20healthy%20dynamic%2C%20Holmes%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BBy%20human%20nature%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20irritate%20each%20other%20because%20nobody's%20perfect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeeling%20irritated%2C%20expressing%20it%20to%20the%20other%20person%2C%20and%20even%20being%20able%20to%20take%20some%20distance%20and%20come%20back%20together%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-healthy-relationship-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esign%20of%20a%20strong%20foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticularly%20if%2C%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20you%20look%20forward%20to%20seeing%20that%20person%20and%20have%20shared%20interests%20and%20common%20goals%2C%20being%20able%20to%20lightheartedly%20pull%20each%20other%20up%20on%20things%20that%20annoy%20you%20can%20be%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIrritation%20can%20be%20a%20reflection%20of%20how%20you're%20feeling%20generally%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20getting%20easily%20annoyed%20by%20someone%2C%20it%20might%2