re.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontroversial-judge-who-praised-modi-to-be-nhrc-chief-opposition-leader-dissents%5C%22%3Eproposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20name%20of%20controversial%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20Arun%20Kumar%20Mishra%2C%20as%20the%20chairperson%20of%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission.%20In%202023%2C%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fretired-sc-judge-s-abdul-nazeer-appointed-as-governor-of-andhra-pradesh%5C%22%3Eappointed%3C%2Fa%3E%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Justice%20S.%20Abdul%20Nazeer%20as%20the%20governor%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20four%20months%20after%20he%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanwilkar%20has%20authored%20key%20judgments%20with%20wide-ranging%20impact%20on%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E377%2C%20Aadhaar%2C%20Sabarimala%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20had%20been%20part%20of%20the%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20Dipak%20Misra%20and%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20Rohinton%20Fali%20Nariman%2C%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20Indu%20Malhotra%2C%20that%20decriminalised%20homosexuality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%202018%2C%20a%20bench%20with%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20in%20it%20upheld%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20Act.%20The%20majority%20opinion%2C%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Sikri%20was%20on%20behalf%20of%20then%20CJI%20Misra%20and%20Justice%20Khanwilkar.%20The%20petitioners%20had%20said%20that%20the%20exercise%20infringed%20upon%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20citizens%2C%20something%20that%20the%20court%20did%20not%20agree%20with.%20Since%20then%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.economictimes.com%2Fwealth%2Fsave%2Fthis-new-aadhaar-related-banking-fraud-is-on-the-rise-why-you-need-to-lock-your-aadhaar-biometrics-now%2Farticleshow%2F104575645.cms%5C%22%3EAadhaar%20frauds%20have%20frequently%20made%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20government%20has%20issued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.economictimes.com%2Fwealth%2Fsave%2Faadhaar-fraud-how-to-prevent-misuse-of-aadhaar-card-details-govt-shares-tips%2Farticleshow%2F103535246.cms%5C%22%3Eguidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20appear%20to%20have%20little%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanwilkar%20was%20also%20part%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20which%20in%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsabarimala-review-petition-verdict%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSeptember%252028%252C%25202018%253A%2520The%2520Supreme%2CMalhotra%2520delivers%2520the%2520dissenting%2520judgment.%5C%22%3Eallowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20entry%20of%20women%20into%20the%20Sabarimala%20temple%20in%20Kerala%2C%20saying%20that%20banning%20women%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20the%20shrine%20is%20gender%20discrimination%20and%20the%20practice%20violates%20rights%20of%20Hindu%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGujarat%20riots%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanwilkar%20was%20part%20of%20the%20bench%20in%202022%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgujarat-riots-zakia-jafri-plea-supreme-court-clean-chit-modi%5C%22%3Edismissed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20plea%20of%20Zakia%20Jafri%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20slain%20MP%20Ehsan%20Jafri%2C%20challenging%20the%20Special%20Investigation%20Team%E2%80%99s%20(SIT)%20clean%20chit%20to%2064%20people%2C%20including%20then%20chief%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20in%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20riots%20case.%20On%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20Police%20had%20on%20the%20following%20day%2C%20arrested%20activist%20Teesta%20Setalvad%20and%20former%20IPS%20officer%20R.%20B.%20Sreekumar%20on%20charges%20of%20fabricating%20evidence%20linked%20to%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20arresting%20and%20detaining%20Teesta%20and%20constituting%20an%20SIT%20apparently%20to%20investigate%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20malign%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20some%20other%20issues%2C%20I%20wonder%20who%20is%20keeping%20the%20pot%20boiling%2C%E2%80%9D%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20Justice%20Madan%20Lokur%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgujarat-police-arrest-teesta-setalvad-activist-who-pursued-2002-riots-case-against-modi%5C%22%3Ewritten%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20controversial%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFCRA%2C%20PMLA%2C%20UAPA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%2C%20heading%20a%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20upheld%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202020.%20The%20Act%20was%20introduced%20to%20regulate%20NGOs%E2%80%99%20access%20to%20foreign%20donors.%20The%20Modi%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fas-three-more-ngos-lose-fcra-licence-a-relook-at-the-govts-funding-restrictions%5C%22%3Efrequently%20stripped%20organisations%20critical%20of%20it%20off%20its%20FCRA%20licences%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%20two%20days%20before%20his%20retirement%2C%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20delivered%20a%20judgment%20that%20give%20enormous%20powers%20to%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20%E2%80%93%20often%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20central%20agency%20of%20choice%20in%20the%20alleged%20intimidation%20of%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20activists.%20The%20court%20said%20Section%2019%20that%20deals%20with%20the%20power%20to%20arrest%20does%20not%20suffer%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvice%20of%20arbitrariness%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20Section%205%20of%20the%20Act%20relating%20to%20the%20attachment%20of%20property%20of%20those%20involved%20in%20money%20laundering%20is%20constitutionally%20valid.%20The%20apex%20court%20also%20said%20the%20supply%20of%20Enforcement%20Case%20Information%20Report%20(ECIR)%20in%20every%20case%20to%20the%20person%20concerned%20is%20not%20mandatory.%20The%20ECIR%20is%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20equivalent%20of%20a%20police%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20legal%20scholar%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20had%20noted%20that%20no%20discussion%20of%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%E2%80%99s%20legacy%20can%20not%20include%20the%202019%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Investigation%20Agency%20vs%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Shah%20Watali%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20involved%20the%20interpretation%20of%20Section%2043(D)(5)%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%2C%20which%20bars%20the%20grant%20of%20bail%20if%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20police%20version%20(through%20the%20case%20diary%20or%20the%20chargesheet)%20against%20the%20accused%20is%2C%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bhatia%E2%80%99s%20words%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Watali%2C%20Justice%20Khanwilkar%20barred%20all%20courts%20from%20%E2%80%9Cexamining%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cdissecting%E2%80%9D%20the%20evidence%2C%20he%20effectively%20made%20the%20grant%20of%20bail%20in%20UAPA%20cases%20borderline%20impossible.%20As%20Sekhri%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheproofofguilt.blogspot.com%2F2019%2F04%2Fbail-in-terror-cases-zahoor-watali-and.html%5C%22%3Ewrote%20at%20the%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20%E2%80%9Cactively%20chose%20a%20legal%20position%20that%20makes%20lengthy%20undertrial%20detention%20more%20likely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709109059000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F29155631%2FScreenshot-2022-07-29-at-3.56.25-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-khanwilkar-lokpal-fcra-pmla-uapa-aadhaar-modi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justice%20Khanwilkar's%20appointment%20continues%20the%20controversial%20tradition%20of%20top%20post-retirement%20positions%20going%20to%20judges%20of%20the%20highest%20court%20of%20the%20country%20after%20retirement.%C2%A0%22%2C