(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F18141356%2FScreenshot-2022-04-18-at-2.13.51-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22987%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F18141356%2FScreenshot-2022-04-18-at-2.13.51-PM.png%20987w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F18141356%2FScreenshot-2022-04-18-at-2.13.51-PM-300x177.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F18141356%2FScreenshot-2022-04-18-at-2.13.51-PM-425x250.png%20425w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-592686%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22583%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20girls%20studying%20in%20school.%20Photo%3A%20TESS%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY-SA%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20this%20framing%2C%20Pratham%20picked%20up%20steam%2C%20gaining%20right%20to%20intervene%20to%20bridge%20the%20gap%20in%20learning.%20Since%20then%2C%20Pratham%20has%20helped%20frame%20education%20policy%2C%20besides%20assisting%20in%20its%20implementation.%20It%20has%20injected%20ideas%2C%20reading%20material%2C%20and%20people%20in%20the%20public%20school%20system.%20ASER%E2%80%99s%20tools%20for%20assessing%20literacy%2C%20used%20extensively%20in%20government%20schools%2C%20are%20seen%20as%20learning%20goals%20in%20themselves.%20Teachers%20do%20regular%20paperwork%20to%20say%20they%20are%20using%20these%20tools%3B%20teachers%E2%80%99%20own%20assessment%20of%20students%E2%80%99%20ability%2C%20a%20key%20tool%20for%20classroom%20interaction%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20count.%20The%20ASER%20survey%20helped%20bury%20the%20no-detention%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20latest%20policy%20intervention%2C%20Pratham%20and%20Central%20Square%20Foundation%2C%20flush%20with%20funds%20from%20Gates%20Foundation%20and%20other%20rich%20donors%2C%20have%20pushed%20FLN%2C%20a%20strange%20concept%20which%20sees%20reading%20as%20a%20mechanical%20skill%2C%20sometimes%20confusing%20it%20with%20fluency%20but%20often%20separating%20it%20from%20comprehension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFLN%20is%20part%20of%20New%20Education%20Policy%20or%20NEP%202020%2C%20and%20has%20begun%20reaching%20schools%20in%20all%20states%20this%20academic%20year%20through%20workbooks%20devised%20by%20State%20Councils%20of%20Educational%20Research%20and%20Training%20or%20SCERTs.%20So%20important%20is%20FLN%20that%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.education.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fupload_files%2Fmhrd%2Ffiles%2FNEP_Final_English_0.pdf%5C%22%3Epolicy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20favourite%20of%20the%20Modi%20regime%2C%20calls%20it%20an%20%E2%80%9Curgent%20national%20mission%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFLN%20will%20intensify%20decontextualised%20and%20rote%20learning%2C%20note%20Martin%20Haus%2C%20who%20is%20doing%20doctoral%20research%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%E2%80%99%20department%20of%20government%20and%20Harvard%20doctoral%20scholar%20Ghosh%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.lse.ac.uk%2Finternationaldevelopment%2F2022%2F04%2F04%2Fis-the-push-for-foundational-numeracy-and-literacy-in-india-pro-poor%2F%5C%22%3Ethis%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDespite%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20%E2%80%9CFLN%20for%20all%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20push%20for%20attaining%20these%20basic%20skills%20is%20almost%20exclusively%20directed%20at%20children%20from%20rural%20and%20marginalized%20communities%20who%20have%20historically%20received%20substandard%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20write%20Haus%20and%20Ghosh.%20The%20blog%20was%20reproduced%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20trouble%20with%20donor%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJournalist%20Tim%20Schwab%20has%20deep%20dived%20into%20the%20influence%20and%20impact%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20in%20education%20in%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America.%20In%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98The%20Bill%20Gates%20Problem%2C%20Reckoning%20with%20the%20Myth%20of%20the%20Good%20Billionaire%E2%80%99%2C%20released%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20Schwab%20shows%20how%20Bill%20Gates%20has%20lit%20fires%20in%20the%20public%20school%20system%20there%20and%20failed%20to%20put%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20interventions%20ranged%20from%20a%20set%20of%20educational%20standards%20called%20the%20Common%20Core%20in%20the%20early%202010s%20that%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20%E2%80%9Cwilled%20into%20existence%E2%80%9D%2C%20says%20Schwab%2C%20to%20eliminating%20so-called%20bad%20teachers%20in%20the%20USA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20aligning%20each%20state%E2%80%99s%20educational%20standards%2C%20and%20relentlessly%20testing%20against%20those%20standards%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20promised%20that%20students%20all%20across%20America%20would%20finally%20have%20access%20to%20the%20same%20high-quality%20education%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGates%20worked%20with%20political%20parties%20and%20%E2%80%9Cleaned%20heavily%20on%20the%20media%20to%20help%20drive%20its%20education%20reform%20agenda%E2%80%9D.%20It%20put%20in%20money%20into%20underwriting%20%C2%A0news%20programmes%2C%20promoted%20a%20documentary%20on%20its%20educational%20reforms%20agenda%2C%20and%20held%20Gates-funded%20summits%20hosted%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Atlantic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20well-known%20magazine%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStates%20in%20that%20country%20began%20adopting%20the%20standards%20before%20a%20final%20draft%20had%20been%20made%20public%20and%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20had%20been%20no%20pilot%20programme%20or%20assessment%20to%20make%20sure%20Common%20Core%20was%20effective.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20called%20it%20one%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20swiftest%20and%20most%20remarkable%20shifts%20in%20education%20policy%20in%20U.S.%20history.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20states%20began%20backtracking%20on%20the%20Common%20Core%20when%20it%20drew%20critics%20from%20both%20the%20left%20and%20the%20right.%20An%20independent%20evaluation%20went%20on%20to%20show%20that%20Common%20Core%20didn%E2%80%99t%20actually%20do%20what%20Gates%20had%20said%20it%20would%2C%20improve%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20interventions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20Pratham%20has%20pushed%20programmes%20and%20ideas%20on%20government-run%20schools%20which%20the%20world%20has%20found%20unacceptable.%20The%20alarm%20bells%20about%20Pratham%2C%20and%20the%20ASER%20survey%E2%80%99s%20impact%2C%20when%20rung%20by%20a%20few%20journalists%2C%20have%20not%20been%20heard.%20It%20stays%20a%20media%20darling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20governments%20were%20segregating%20children%20in%20the%20same%20age%20group%20in%20school%2C%20making%20them%20sit%20in%20separate%20classrooms%2C%20and%20even%20teaching%20them%20from%20different%20textbooks%20%E2%80%93%20said%20to%20be%20based%20on%20their%20ability%2C%20part%20of%20teaching-to-test%20or%20Teach%20at%20the%20Right%20Level%2C%20a%20move%20pushed%20by%20Pratham%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdelhi-schools-ability-based-grouping%5C%22%3EI%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Delhi%20government%E2%80%99s%20effort%2C%20and%20its%20disastrous%20impact%20on%20children%20and%20the%20way%20they%20perceived%20each%20other%2C%20recorded%20by%20an%20intern%20teacher%20who%20studied%20the%20impact%20over%20months.%20Manish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20research%20found%20that%20physical%20separation%20changed%20the%20identity%20of%20students.%20They%20began%20calling%20their%20classmates%20not%20by%20their%20names%20but%20by%20the%20group%20name%2C%20and%20even%20refused%20to%20play%20with%20the%20group%20perceived%20as%20weak%20in%20ability.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20anything%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20you%20are%20in%20Vishwas%20(lower-ability%20group)%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20student%20reported%20being%20told.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F709142131%2Fcontent%3Fstart_page%3D1%26view_mode%3Dscroll%26access_key%3Dkey-bVcTgcAKxuv4SEZM9sl5%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20data-auto-height%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%220.7068965517241379%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Manish%20Kumar%20Peace%20Education%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F709142131%2FManish-Kumar-Peace-Education%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20Manish%20Kumar%20Peace%20Education%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EManish%20Kumar%20Peace%20Education%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fuser%2F286754081%2FThe-Wire%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20The%20Wire's%20profile%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20feels%20angry%20with%20himself%20for%20not%20having%20enough%20brains%20to%20be%20in%20the%20Pratibha%20section.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20less%20brain%2C%20that%20is%20why%20Pratibha%20section%20does%20not%20play%20with%20me.%20I%20wish%20I%20could%20study%20like%20Pratibha%20section%2C%20and%20be%20in%20the%20Pratibha%20section.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20shows%20an%20impact%20on%20vulnerable%20minds.%20Experts%20pointed%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20peer%20learning%20that%20such%20a%20policy%20of%20segregation%20entails.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20reporting%20on%20ability-based%20segregation%20in%202019%2C%20I%20sat%20down%20with%20Shailendra%20Sharma%2C%20principal%20advisor%2C%20director%20of%20education%2C%20Delhi%20government%20for%20nearly%20two%20hours%20to%20understand%20the%20logic%20behind%20the%20ability%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharma%20drew%20his%20salary%20from%20Pratham.%20He%20had%20a%20substantial%20office%20and%20team%20in%20the%20old%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20parent%20decided%20to%20sue%20the%20Delhi%20Government%2C%20forcing%20it%20on%20the%20back%20foot.%20The%20Delhi%20Government%20gave%20the%20segregation%20a%20quiet%20burial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPratham%20didn%E2%80%99t%20reply%20to%20my%20question%20on%20whether%20it%20has%20done%20any%20study%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20physically%20segregating%20students%20by%20ability%2C%20and%20FLN%2C%20and%20said%20these%20queries%20are%20better%20addressed%20to%20the%20Delhi%20government.%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20organisation%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20done%20any%20studies%20on%20either%20and%20chose%20to%20clump%20both%20as%20the%20Delhi%20government%E2%80%99s%20Mission%20Buniyaad%20policy%2C%20though%20FLN%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Union%20Government%E2%80%99s%20new%20education%20policy%2C%20and%20has%20begun%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%20schools%20country-wide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20did%20not%20reply%20to%20my%20question%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20interventions%20on%20teachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETeacher%2C%20teacher%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeachers%20are%20wary%20of%20repeated%20Pratham%20interventions%20because%20they%20have%20seen%20the%20NGO%E2%80%99s%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20constantly%20highlighting%20failure%2C%20Pratham%20has%20eroded%20the%20professional%20credibility%20of%20teachers%2C%20teachers%20I%20met%20with%20say%2C%20especially%20those%20working%20in%20government%20schools.%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20interventions%20in%20government%20schools%20have%20included%20preparing%20%E2%80%98teacher-proof%E2%80%99%20material%20which%20just%20needs%20to%20be%20delivered%20by%20any%20adult.%20This%20re-constitutes%20teaching%20as%20a%20non-profession%20and%20as%20%E2%80%98service%E2%80%99%20or%20as%20%E2%80%98volunteering%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20big%20part%20of%20NEP%202020.%20This%20impacts%20teacher%20recruitment%2C%20already%20an%20area%20where%20state%20governments%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fwhy-indias-richest-state-cannot-hire-enough-teachers-47765%2F%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20want%20to%20spend%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20brings%20in%20contractual%20jobs%20where%20teachers%20have%20neither%20rights%20nor%20full%20salaries.%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20tool%20for%20assessing%20literacy%20has%20come%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20learning%20goal%20in%20itself.%20It%20is%20used%20extensively%20in%20government%20primary%20schools%20to%20assess%20and%20segregate%20children%20merely%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20performance%20on%20the%20tool.%20This%20erodes%20the%20teacher%E2%80%99s%20own%20assessment%20of%20her%20students%E2%80%99%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F19172620%2F5537220987_a3314f6706_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22school%20children%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F19172620%2F5537220987_a3314f6706_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F19172620%2F5537220987_a3314f6706_b-300x135.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-414539%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20school%20children.%20Photo%3A%20Maia%20Maia%2FFlickr%2C%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20through%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20work%20in%20schools%20and%20the%20more%20recent%20but%20more%20decisive%20role%20in%20policy-making%20itself%2C%20they%20have%20succeeded%20in%20de-professionalising%20teachers%20by%20taking%20away%20their%20agency%20at%20all%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20content%20planning%20and%20delivery%2C%20classroom%20dynamics%20and%20organisation%2C%20and%20assessment%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20teacher%20who%20has%20headed%20a%20group%20of%20teachers%20who%20have%20analysed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20unsuccessfully%20tried%20to%20raise%20questions%20on%20%E2%80%93%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeachers%20in%20Delhi%20report%20that%20Pratham%E2%80%99s%20summer%20reading%20camps%20have%20ended%20the%20summer%20break%20for%20teachers%2C%20something%20they%20looked%20forward%20to%20after%20a%20tiring%20term%20and%20end-of-year%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20part%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20education%20reform%20agenda%2C%20at%20one%20time%2C%20was%20eliminating%20bad%20teachers%20in%20the%20USA%2C%20reports%20Schwab%20in%20his%20book.%20Gates%20advanced%20an%20agenda%20to%20weed%20out%20low%20performers%20and%20reward%20the%20best%20teachers.%20A%20pilot%20project%20in%20Hillsborough%2C%20Florida%20ended%20in%20disaster.%20But%20before%20its%20failure%2C%20the%20heavily-promoted%20project%20had%20%E2%80%9Ccontributed%20to%20a%20nationwide%20zeitgeist%20of%20teacher%20accountability%20efforts%E2%80%94and%20a%20culture%20of%20blaming%20teachers%20for%20the%20poor%20performance%20of%20students.%20One%20teacher%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20after%20having%20been%20publicly%20named%20as%20a%20low-performing%20teacher%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3ELos%20Angeles%20Times%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecommitted%20suicide%2C%20prompting%20hundreds%20of%20students%2C%20teachers%20and%20parents%20to%20protest%20outside%20the%20newspaper%E2%80%99s%20office%E2%80%9D%2C%20writes%20Schwab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiddle%20school%20teacher%20and%20writer%20Anthony%20Cody%20noted%20that%20for%20all%20Bill%20Gates%E2%80%99s%20rhetoric%20about%20using%20a%20variety%20of%20measurements%20in%20teacher%20evaluation%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20had%20carefully%20crafted%20its%20teacher%20evaluation%20metrics%20around%20student%20test%20scores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6if%20the%20Foundation%20was%20really%20the%20organization%20it%20claims%20to%20be%2C%20working%20in%20partnerships%20with%20teachers%20and%20communities%2C%20it%20would%20publicly%20apologise%20for%20its%20failures%20and%20offer%20compensation%20and%20reparations%20for%20all%20the%20harm%20it%20has%20caused%2C%20from%20the%20teacher-shaming%20culture%20it%20engendered%20to%20the%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20taxpayer%20dollars%20that%20were%20spent%2C%20or%20wasted%2C%20on%20its%20failed%20pilot%20project%20in%20Hillsborough%20County%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Schwab%20in%20his%20book%20on%20the%20Gates%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPratham%20has%20similarly%20not%20apologised%20for%20the%20harm%20caused%20by%20segregating%20students%20in%20schools%20in%20India.%20Probably%20the%20subjects%20who%20are%20experimented%20upon%2C%20children%20in%20government-run%20schools%2C%20did%20not%20deserve%20an%20apology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnding%20no-detention%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPratham%E2%80%99s%20Aser%20reports%20sounded%20the%20death%20knell%20on%20the%20move%20not%20to%20detain%20young%20students%20in%20both%20private%20and%20government%20schools%20%E2%80%93%20a%20move%20which%20sought%20to%20stem%20student%20suicides%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Aser%20reports%20are%20perhaps%20the%20most%20frequently-cited%20of%20all%20education%20surveys%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F865593%2Fwhy-more-and-more-parents-are-going-for-private-schools-director-of-influential-education-survey%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20Shreya%20Roy%20Chowdhury%2C%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20covered%20education%20for%20many%20years%2C%20for%20%3Cem%3EScroll%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIts%20findings%20are%20invoked%20to%20lobby%20for%20or%20resist%20a%20variety%20of%20policy%20decisions.%20They%20help%20buttress%20arguments%20in%20favour%20of%20removing%20the%20no-detention%20policy%20from%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%20Act%2C%202009%2C%20which%20mandated%20the%20promotion%20of%20all%20children%20between%20Classes%201-8%20every%20year%20regardless%20of%20performance.%20Its%20data%20comparing%20learning%20outcomes%20of%20children%20studying%20in%20government%20schools%20with%20those%20enrolled%20in%20private%20ones%2C%20without%20considering%20non-school%20factors%20such%20caste%2C%20income%20or%20education%20or%20parents%2C%20are%20invariably%20cited%20to%20push%20for%20deregulation%20of%20private%20schools%20and%20even%20to%20challenge%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%20Act.%20The%20Act%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20on%20what%20it%20calls%20%E2%80%9Cinputs%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20schools%20have%20basic%20infrastructure%20such%20as%20toilets%20and%20classrooms%20and%20resources%20like%20qualified%20teachers%20%E2%80%93%20to%20be%20recognised%2C%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20hindrance%20to%20private%20enterprise%20in%20education.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoy%20Chowdhury%20asks%20ASER%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20Wilima%20Wadhwa%20in%20the%20interview%20why%20the%20ASER%20surveys%20always%20paint%20a%20dismal%20picture%2C%20and%20why%20the%20data%20does%20not%20factor%20in%20caste%20and%20family%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoy%20Chowdhury%3A%20Your%20reports%20are%20used%20to%20buttress%20arguments%20to%20remove%20the%20ban%20on%20detention%20in%20primary%20school%20from%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%20Act.%20Do%20you%20have%20a%20stand%20on%20this%20issue%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWadhwa%3A%20We%20have%20never%20had%20a%20stance%20on%20it.%20You%20know%20it%20will%20have%20certain%20consequences%20and%20one%20of%20them%20is%20this%20%5Blow%20outcomes%5D.%20Am%20I%20saying%20holding%20back%20a%20child%20is%20a%20good%20thing%3F%20No!%20Of%20course%20not.%20But%20the%20survey%20results%20are%20an%20early%20warning%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInformally%2C%20many%20states%20already%20had%20a%20no-detention%20policy%20up%20to%20Class%205.%20We%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20watershed%20years%20%E2%80%93%20the%20end%20of%20primary%20school%20%5BClass%205%5D%20was%20one%20and%20that%20is%20when%20many%20dropped%20out.%20The%20jumps%20in%20curriculum%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Class%205%20to%206%20and%20from%20Class%208%20to%209%20%E2%80%93%20are%20different%20from%20the%20changes%20from%20Class%204%20to%205%20and%20Class%207%20to%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20where%20they%20will%20face%20most%20difficulty.%20Do%20not%20hold%20the%20child%20back%20but%20there%20has%20to%20be%20some%20way%20of%20addressing%20the%20deficit.%20Learning%20levels%20were%20low%20and%20slow%20to%20change%20from%202005%20to%202010%2C%20but%20after%202010%2C%20there%20was%20a%20drop.%20Suddenly%20the%20focus%20shifted%20to%20playgrounds%20and%20boundary%20walls.%20I%20am%20not%20saying%20those%20are%20not%20important%20but%20whatever%20little%20attention%20learning%20got%20also%20went%20away.%20The%20teachers%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20elections%20and%20Census%20%5Benumeration%5D%20along%20with%20continuous%20comprehensive%20evaluation%20%5Bmandated%20by%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%20Act%2C%20it%20involves%20constant%20tracking%20of%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20progress%20in%20place%20of%20a%20year-end%20exam%5D%20which%20took%20years%20to%20figure%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20also%20been%20accused%20of%20constantly%20testing%20a%20child%20leading%20to%20stress%20%E2%80%93%20but%20unless%20you%20know%20where%20the%20deficits%20are%2C%20how%20will%20you%20address%20them%3F%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy-making%20is%20like%20a%20patchwork%20%E2%80%93%20you%20have%20a%20crisis%20somewhere%2C%20you%20put%20a%20patch%20over%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20no-detention%20policy%2C%20backed%20by%20CCE%20or%20comprehensive%20and%20continuous%20evaluation%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20changes%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20exam-driven%20school%20education.%20The%20policy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fparliament-approves-bill-to-reverse-no-detention-policy-till-class-8%5C%22%3Egot%20short%20shrift%20from%20Parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%202018%2C%20just%20a%20few%20days%20before%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20interview.%20Prakash%20Javadekar%2C%20the%20minister%20responsible%20for%20education%20then%2C%20said%2025%20states%20had%20asked%20for%20the%20right%20to%20scrap%20%E2%80%98no%20detention%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20children%20as%20young%20as%2010%20could%20be%20said%20to%20%E2%80%98fail%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20then%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20reason%20why%20governments%20end%20up%20courting%20interventions%20in%20education%20is%20that%20education%20is%20a%20slow-reform%20sector.%20The%20impact%20of%20an%20educated%20society%2C%20given%20to%20critical%20thinking%2C%20cannot%20be%20measured%20in%20simple%20metrics.%20Or%20farmed%20for%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20visible%20is%20a%20student%20who%20reads%20aloud%20fluently%20without%20understanding%20anything.%20The%20parents%2C%20at%20least%2C%20will%20be%20satisfied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20student%20failure%20is%20a%20result%20of%20deep%20wealth%20inequities%20which%20politicians%20would%20not%20like%20to%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriter%20and%20middle%20school%20teacher%20Cody%2C%20a%20leading%20critic%20of%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20notes%20in%20the%20book%20by%20Schwab%2C%20that%20academic%20success%20is%20predominantly%20guided%20by%20factors%20%3Cem%3Eoutside%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20school%20related%20to%20wealth%20and%20social%20class.%20This%20means%20Gates%E2%80%99s%20classroom%20interventions%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20changing%20educational%20standards%2C%20supporting%20charter%20schools%2C%20evaluating%20teachers%2C%20or%20introducing%20new%20educational%20software%20%E2%80%93%20can%E2%80%99t%20deliver%20the%20game-changing%20results%20the%20foundation%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20solve%20the%20problem%20of%20educational%20inequity%20while%20we%20ignore%20the%20inequitable%20and%20inadequate%20resources%20available%20to%20low-income%20children%20in%20their%20homes%20and%20communities%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20schools%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cody%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESchwab%20interrogates%20Bill%20Gates%E2%80%99s%20own%20education%20in%20an%20elite%2C%20private%20school%20and%20then%20at%20Harvard%2C%20which%20allowed%20Gates%20self-exploration%20to%20develop%20a%20sense%20of%20self-confidence%20and%20an%20identity%20to%20decide%20which%20subjects%20he%20needed%20to%20study%20further.%20It%20also%20gave%20him%20free%20time%20to%20get%20his%20first%20job%20in%20senior%20year%20in%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGates%20has%20given%20his%20own%20children%20the%20same%20rich%20educational%20experiences%20he%20had%2C%20but%20he%20has%20been%20far%20less%20charitable%20towards%20the%20poor%20children%20of%20colour%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20his%20philanthropic%20efforts.%20For%20the%20masses%20and%20the%20commoners%2C%20education%20is%20not%20about%20enlightenment%20or%20critical%20thinking%20or%20creativity%20or%20dignity%20or%20self-discovery%20or%20even%20learning.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20getting%20the%20necessary%20training%20to%20be%20useful%20contributors%20to%20the%20global%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20writes%20Schwab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20exactly%20what%20India%E2%80%99s%20school%20education%20is%20pushing%20common%20people%20towards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709105315000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2F10365240914_2dcd75a526_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fhow-rich-donors-have-caused-more-harm-than-good-to-indias-education%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20India%2C%20NGOs%20like%20Pratham%20have%20pushed%20programmes%20and%20ideas%20on%20government-run%20schools%20which%20the%20world%20has%20found%20unac