j%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20after%20the%20general%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomewhere%20along%20the%20line%2C%20there%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20a%20last%20minute%20change%20of%20heart%2C%20evidenced%20by%20the%20publication%20of%20a%2027-page%20factsheet%20before%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20no%20reason%20for%20this%20has%20been%20provided%2C%20what%20is%20certain%20is%20that%20no%20sooner%20was%20the%20factsheet%20released%20than%20the%20narrative%20started%20to%20build%20about%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20ending%20poverty.%20The%20Niti%20Aayog%20stated%20that%20poverty%20had%20declined%20to%20less%20than%205%25%20and%20applauded%20the%20government%20for%20achieving%20this%20feat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20prudent%20to%20understand%20that%20the%2027-pager%20HCES%20%5B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F09a7d8be-f242-404b-a3a1-1c79eab489ea%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F09a7d8be-f242-404b-a3a1-1c79eab489ea%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1709174235978000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1k4goLsnKkvyK3XvxHz3Lj%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPDF%3C%2Fa%3E%5D%20says%20nothing%20about%20the%20poverty%20decline%20in%202022-23%20as%20compared%20to%202011-12.%20Rather%20it%20goes%20ahead%20and%20cautions%20readers%20about%20the%20change%20in%20methodology%20in%20the%20current%20HCES%20as%20compared%20to%20earlier%20ones.%20The%20factsheet%20lists%20various%20%E2%80%9CIssues%20related%20to%20Comparability%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20HCES%202022-23%20has%20undergone%20methodological%20changes%2C%20its%20results%20ought%20not%20to%20be%20compared%20with%20the%20previous%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%20(CES).%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20National%20Survey%20Organisation%20(NSO)%2C%20which%20conducts%20these%20surveys%2C%20has%20personally%20informed%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20that%20the%20HCES%20is%20not%20comparable%20with%20the%20earlier%20CES.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20Niti%20Aayog%20CEO%2C%20who%20also%20knows%20this%20surely%2C%20went%20ahead%20and%20compared%20the%20current%20survey%20with%20earlier%20ones%20in%20claiming%20poverty%20reduction.%20Bear%20inn%20mind%20that%20the%20Niti%20Aayog%20has%20no%20current%20poverty%20line%20by%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20the%20erstwhile%20Planning%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20by%20which%20to%20measure%20the%20current%20level%20of%20poverty.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20would%20be%20curious%20to%20argue%20that%20consumption%20expenditure%20is%20rising%20when%20real%20wages%20have%20been%20stagnating%20in%20recent%20years%3B%20yet%20that%20is%20exactly%20what%20representatives%20of%20the%20government%20have%20used%20HCES%202023%20data%20to%20argue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20HCES%202022-23%2C%20the%20sampling%20methodology%20has%20undergone%20significant%20change.%20Second%20stage%20stratum%20classification%20is%20now%20made%20on%20land%20for%20rural%20areas%20and%20car%20availability%20for%20urban%20areas%2C%20unlike%20the%20previous%20survey%20where%20the%20divisions%20were%20made%20based%20on%20household%20status%20and%20household%20activity%20for%20rural%20areas%20and%20monthly%20per-capita%20income%20for%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20country%20where%20agricultural%20labourers%20outnumber%20cultivators%2C%20access%20to%20land%20remains%20limited%20let%20alone%20possessing%20land%20amongst%20the%20highest%20order%20as%20classified%20in%20the%20top%20two%20second-stage%20stratum.%20For%20urban%20areas%2C%20households%20were%20classified%20based%20on%20the%20availability%20of%20four-wheeler%20cars%2C%20with%20a%20price%20of%20more%20than%20Rs%2010%20Lakh%2C%20price%20less%20than%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20and%20households%20without%20cars.%20In%20a%20country%20where%208%25%20of%20households%20own%20a%20car%2C%20the%20urban%20second%20stratum%20will%20be%20among%20the%20wealthiest%20households.%20Thus%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20higher%20representation%20of%20the%20well-off%20groups%20in%20the%20HCES%202022-23%20sampling%20approach%2C%20thereby%20resulting%20in%20higher%20consumption%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HCES%202022-23%20factsheet%20lists%20various%20methodological%20changes%20as%20well.%20The%20number%20of%20items%20covered%20has%20increased%20from%20347%20to%20405%20items.%20Instead%20of%20a%20single%20questionnaire%2C%20HCES%202022-23%20uses%20four%20separate%20questionnaires%20to%20be%20canvassed%20in%20three%20separate%20monthly%20visits%20in%20a%20quarter%20instead%20of%20the%20usual%20practice%20of%20a%20single%20visit.%20Therefore%20on%20account%20of%20methodological%20changes%20alone%2C%20the%20results%20of%20the%20current%20HCES%20are%20not%20strictly%20comparable%20with%20the%202011-12%20CES%20or%20the%20earlier%20CES.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHCES%202022-23%20states%20that%20the%20average%20monthly%20per-capita%20consumption%20expenditure%20(MPCE)%20at%20current%20prices%20has%20increased%20to%20Rs%203%2C773%20for%20rural%20households%20and%20Rs%206%2C459%20for%20urban%20households.%20These%20numbers%20have%20been%20used%20in%20order%20to%20claim%20that%20poverty%20in%20India%20has%20fallen%20to%20just%205%25%2C%20even%20though%20the%20factsheet%20does%20not%20make%20any%20reference%20to%20poverty%20eradication%2C%20nor%20is%20there%20any%20poverty%20line%20given%20by%20the%20HCES.%20So%20how%20has%20this%20claim%20that%20poverty%20has%20fallen%20been%20made%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2027-page%20factsheet%20is%20mostly%20based%20on%20ratios%20and%20proportions.%20There%20are%20no%20comparisons%20with%20real%20amounts.%20From%20the%20comparative%20perspective%2C%20a%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20needs%20to%20be%20used%20to%20deflate%20current%20expenditure%20to%20arrive%20at%20real%20expenditure.%20In%20making%20comparisons%20over%20the%20years%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20data%20on%20real%20expenditure%20and%20quantity%20of%20consumption.%20Additionally%2C%20HCES%202022-23%20takes%20into%20account%20the%20imputed%20value%20of%20social-welfare%20programmes%2C%20though%20the%20same%20was%20not%20undertaken%20for%20the%20earlier%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20economic%20growth%20and%20progress%2C%20the%20share%20of%20food%20expenditure%20in%20total%20household%20expenditure%20is%20bound%20to%20come%20down.%20The%20current%20level%20of%20food%20expenditure%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%2046.38%25%20(for%20rural%20households)%20and%2039.17%25%20(for%20urban%20households)%20%E2%80%93%20remains%20comparatively%20very%20high%20as%20compared%20to%206.4%25%20for%20USA%20and%206.9%25%20for%20Singapore%2C%20and%20thus%20cannot%20be%20taken%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20economic%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20how%20can%20poverty%20have%20fallen%20when%20job%20growth%20and%20real%20wages%20have%20come%20down%3F%20While%20from%202004-05%20to%202011-12%20there%20was%20an%20unmistakable%20and%20sustained%20rise%20in%20real%20wages%2C%20wages%20have%20stagnated%20between%202013%20and%202017.%20Additionally%2C%20joblessness%20grew%20from%2010%20million%20in%202011-12%20to%20nearly%2038%20million%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20190%20million%20workers%20(2021-22)%20in%20India%20are%20earning%20just%20up%20to%20Rs.%20100%20per%20day%20(in%20real%20terms%20at%202010%20prices)%20which%20can%20be%20categorised%20as%20absolute%20poor%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20just%20106.1%20million%20workers%20in%202011-12.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20massive%20surge%20in%20the%20number%20of%20poor%20workers%20in%20recent%20times.%20There%20are%20144.0%20million%20workers%20(2021-22)%20that%20are%20earning%20between%20Rs%20100%20and%20Rs%20200%20per%20day%20which%20can%20be%20categorised%20as%20poor%20and%20vulnerable.%20Additionally%2C%20there%20are%20still%20127.5%20million%20workers%20(2021-22)%20who%20earn%20between%20Rs%20200%20and%20Rs%20300%20per%20day%2C%20which%20can%20be%20categorised%20as%20non-poor%20but%20definitely%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20working%20poor%20and%20the%20decline%20in%20real%20wages%20indicate%20the%20need%20for%20interrogating%20labour%20market%20conditions%20in%20India%2C%20before%20jumping%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20India%20has%20been%20able%20to%20end%20poverty.%20The%20CES%202022-23%20is%20being%20read%20to%20mean%20what%20cannot%20be%20found%20in%20it%20nor%20inferred%20from%20it%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20Visiting%20Professor%20of%20Development%20Economics%2C%20Centre%20for%20Development%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Bath%2C%20UK.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERakesh%20Ranjan%20Kumar%20is%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%2C%20International%20Institute%20for%20Migration%20and%20Development%2C%20Trivandrum.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709097144000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F28104109%2F1339849094_15ec84bbc4_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-truth-behind-the-governments-claim-that-poverty-has-fallen-to-just-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20no%20reason%20for%20this%20has%20been%20provided%2C%20what%20is%20certain%20is%20that%20no%20sooner%20was%20the%20factsheet%20released%20than%20the%20narrative%20started%20to%20build%20about%20the%20governmen